Overall, Big time Rush's Second album "Elevate" would get a 7/10, a poor start section, but it did pick up near the end quite well.

2-13 "Epic" The final track Of Elevate. A very Dance heavy track, nothing unique in general, but it is for these boys. It leans heavily on the beat. So it may not be for everyone, but it is for me. Strong ending. 9/10
2-12 "Elevate" The titular track, It has a very sci-fi techno Instrumental, just like "Big night" from the first album, it's a party track. But it's done very well this time. 8.5/10

2-11 "You're not alone" Very very classic boyband, legit would not be suprised if this was a cover of Blue, with once again what seems to be a Beyoncé inspired instrumental, its, alright I guess. I can't fault it. 6.5/10
2-10 "Superstar" this sounds like a One Direction song(also happy 10th anniversary lol), To be honest this style doesn't fit BTR as much, but they did a good effort at it. 7/10
2-9 "time of our lives" It is genuinely a bop, Its hard to talk about, it's just very disco like with some unique sounds and synths. May not be everyone's cup of tea tho. 8/10

2-8 "Invisible" A suprisingly uplifting song, Even though it's not the best song I would reccomend a listen to this if your down, it has nice stringed instruments and a solo drum, although the instrumental can be a bit slow at times. 7.5/10

2-7 "If I ruled the world(Feat. Iyaz)" First things first, this is probably the closest thing to their first album so far, but quite more refined with a nice guitar and synth, A nice near accapella breakdown, Plus Iyaz brought an enjoyable aspect to the song. 9/10

2-6 "Love me Love me" A more pop focused song, with a near chiptune instrumental, with really interesting breakdowns and use of Autotune, very retro game inspired, a super catchy hook and rap bridge, and an amazing return to form. 10/10

2-5 "Cover Girl" The song's subject is basically, You're the most beautiful person to me, and they do it very well, with a stripped back guitar and drum, with usually 2 boys singing at a time, a very well put together song. 8.5/10

2-4"No Idea" This is probably the first proper stinker, the Instrumental Drones on and on with little to no variation, aside from some High hats here and there along with being very dull as is. This isn't great from the Boys's part as well, They're just as droney as the beat 3/10

2-3"All over again"A very slow start, however it does pick up, James is Easily the Focus on this song, and he does bring it, he fits the song well with a nice back and forth Between Carlos and Logan near the end. BUT the song is very samey through, and I don't like the hook. 5/10

2-2 "Show me" this song has a nice bounce to it, although the instrumental seems a little out of sync at parts. I can easily tell it's a Kendel(Once again if that's his name lol) focused song, which he does a good job on. Through the song there's also a lovely piano riff. 8/10

2-1 "Music Sounds Better(Feat. Mann)" This sounds like a weird Fusion of a modern Dance Song hit, like Lighter By KSI for Example, or Roses, but at the same time it feels like a classic mid 2000's boyband hit, although it did come out in 2012, A nice opener. 7.5/10
@lilboiallan Absolutely 😔✌
@lilboiallan https://t.co/z1omrf1pnv

1-Bonus-3"Til I forget about you Halatrax Remix" Is very similar to the original, but with a techno Synth riff in the back, a slider on the second verse that does sound admittedly nice. If the Tempo changed or something more drastic, I'd probably like it alot more, but as is 7/10

1-Bonus-2 "Till I forget about you Cash-Cash Remix" To any fans of Sonic the Hedgehog, this will be very familiar. The Lego Ninjago comparison applies here again, but the retro Feel actually adds to it in a positive way. 9/10

1-Bonus-1 "Boyfriend(Feat. Snoop Dogg)" The instrumental suits Snoop well, but his first Verse is incredibly short, lasting about 16 bars, He then drops another 16(and alot worse) bars and that's the only difference. So as a remix, I'd give it 5/10, but the song itself, 8.5/10

1-14 - "Stuck" A nice R&B slow jam, reminds me of the Songs Nelly would come out with, but this has a really nice aucostic guitar doing short chords, with electric breakdowns. The instrumental is always changing, however the Vocals seem weak on this track aside from James's. 7/10

1-13"this is our someday" The hook and instrumental doesn't match the rest of the song at all, I much prefer the verses with the guitar
Riffs and the synth. The bridge sounds alright, it links with the course really well with a synth pad breakdown, showcasing the vocals well 7/10

1-12 "Any kind of guy" it sounds like a sequal to the track before sonically, although the subject is different. Although the instrumental isn't nearly as good, execpt for the end, I love the hook, and the auto tuned adlibs, along with James riffing in the background. 9/10
1-11 "Big Time Rush" There's a reason it was the show's opening. With a booming hook, a rad electric guitar at first riffing, then shredding, with chants and a catchy hook. An EASY 10/10

1-10 "I know you know(feat. Cymphonique)" Another slow jam, but the hook is very very catchy, it has a very short acoustic guitar that turns electric with synth pads that I like alot. I didn't care too much for the feature tho. 7.5/10

1-9 "Count on you (feat Jordin Sparks)" a nice love duet Piano Ballad, very Boybandish, and the instrumental sounds like a classic Beyoncé song. Way more harmony in this compared to all the previous songs. 8.5/10

1-8 "oh yeah" this is like the previous song, however on the verses its way better, with a really slick electric bass line, and a wonderful Synthesizer breakdown with nice Vocals from Kendel(if that's his name lol) 9/10
1-7 "Big night" This is, it's tough. I like this song, but, it's a party song, and it's super low energy, so it kinda fails at it's job. 5/10
1-6 "halfway there" Is such a good feel good Triumphant song, where each of the members have equal shine, Great retro Instrumental, absolute Banger. 10/10
1-5 "Worldwide" a much more harmonic, R&B inspired song. I'm not a huge fan of the course but I am a sucker for harmonic vocals. 8/10

1-4 "Nothing even matters" Please note that I barely watched the show back in the day, and that was a long time ago so if I get this wrong oof. But this song had a good bit more focus on Carlos which is nice, but overall it's a pretty decent love ballad. 7/10
1-3 "the city is ours" well its a more generic pop song, fiting of the time period Ig, I liked the vocals on this track tho 6.5/10
1-2 "Boyfriend" was always one of my favourites from when I watched the show back in the day, still holds up and is just as catchy with that great up tempo percussion 10/10
1-1 "Till I forget about you" sounds like a smooth, slightly slower version of the ninjago opening. However there is a smooth breakdown right before the last course. 8/10
